---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { ArrowUpRight } from 'lucide-react';

const updated = '2026-05-02';
const formatted = new Date(updated).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' });
---

<Base title="Now" description="What I'm working on right now. Following the /now convention.">
  <article class="pt-32 pb-32 sm:pt-40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 sm:px-8">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-mint">/ now</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl text-balance">
        What I'm working on.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs text-paper-muted">last updated {formatted}</p>

      <div class="mt-16 space-y-12 prose prose-invert max-w-none
        prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:tracking-tight
        prose-h2:mt-12 prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:font-semibold
        prose-p:text-paper-dim prose-p:text-pretty prose-p:leading-relaxed
        prose-strong:text-paper
        prose-a:text-paper prose-a:underline prose-a:decoration-violet/40 prose-a:underline-offset-4 hover:prose-a:decoration-violet
        prose-li:text-paper-dim
      ">

        <h2>Day job</h2>
        <p>
          Still at <a href="https://portfoliopilot.com">PortfolioPilot</a>, still owning AI surfaces. Right now: the next generation of the eval system, deeper agent tool-use, and a few user-facing AI features that are still under wraps.
        </p>

        <h2>Side</h2>
        <p>
          Rebuilt this site from the ground up — the version you're reading now is hand-crafted in Astro, deployed on Cloudflare, and includes a "chat with my career" feature I'm still tightening. The old site was a 2017 jQuery template and it had served its purpose.
        </p>

        <h2>Reading</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The latest stack of <a href="https://www.alignmentforum.org">Alignment Forum</a> posts on agent evaluation.</li>
          <li><em>Designing Data-Intensive Applications</em>, again. It rewards re-reading.</li>
          <li>Whatever <a href="https://simonwillison.net">Simon Willison</a> has shipped this week.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Learning</h2>
        <p>
          Espresso. Specifically: the gap between "I made coffee" and "I made the same coffee twice in a row."
        </p>

        <h2>Open to</h2>
        <p>
          Founding-engineer or first-AI-engineer conversations at AI-forward seed/Series A teams. Also happy to consult on AI eval / agent infra for short engagements with teams who already know they need it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 flex items-center justify-between border-t border-white/5 pt-8">
        <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" class="group inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-paper-muted transition-colors hover:text-paper">
          what is /now?
          <ArrowUpRight className="h-3 w-3" />
        </a>
        <a href="/about" class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-widest text-paper-muted transition-colors hover:text-paper">/ about →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
